data.content:
noun
plural -cies
formal
[noncount] :the state or fact of living in a place
proof of residency [=residence]
You must meet the town's residency requirement in order to vote.
[singular] :a period of time when someone lives in a place
a four-year residency in the country
[count] :legal permission to live in a place
He was granted/denied residency. [=residence]
[count, noncount] chiefly US :a period when a doctor receives advanced training at a hospital in order to become a specialist in a particular field of medicine
She recently completed her residency in pediatrics.
a residency program
[count, noncount] :a period of time when a writer, artist, etc., lives and works at a college or other institution

Danh từ
phủ thống sứ; toà công sứ (ở các nước thuộc địa hoặc nửa thuộc địa)
